# IQ-ME — per-language reviewer-of-record discipline (FR49, NFR29).
#
# Branch protection (configured in Epic 7) will require BOTH a maintainer
# review AND the per-language reviewer-of-record review before merging any
# non-EN content-key change. At v0.0.1 the per-language reviewers are
# placeholders pending Gate 9c (RU) and Gate 9d (PL) outreach close.
#
# Format reminder: <pattern> <owner1> <owner2> ...
# `@TBD-*` handles are intentionally NOT real GitHub usernames — they
# fail CODEOWNERS resolution, which is the signal to the future
# lint-trust-artifacts.mjs (Story 1.6 / 1.9) that the reviewer-of-record
# is still un-resolved. Do NOT replace these with real handles until the
# corresponding Gate (9c/9d) is documented as closed in CHANGELOG.md.

# Default: project maintainers own the repo.
* @Bulrock

